[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating factory behavior**\n\nI'm considering how multimap works when putting values for the key \"letters.\" It creates a shared list, populates it, and the supplier holds that same list. The writeObject handles this by writing the factory, which has a list like [\"a\", \"b\"], and a backing map that connects \"letters\" to that list. When reading, the factory should return the same list used before. It's important, though, that a factory typically returns empty lists, but this one may not do so after operations. I need to think if adding new keys is necessary and consider asserting existing ones.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d3955b965e3e6dd0169f64557a5d4819588c73c644f8318fd\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9kVhHyktzaQCM4DnQw69yN0u1rI2dGjLHc6QhJBMhlN7bNqEKtQePma7qgUj1NAJai0P_x5NfohdA5GYFZO2ciDw2NJ2AE5gYCF4NpO1bSQtTl3FNc1IGBLHL3rYLJiJt8h9vwIKUTgSyCpV5wB6drsirXS3AXCxNKFLHli7SE5_fqXkumLDTUqOYT-JVe8I0r-2d3DprUXdlen77Z3jCeaHdQ7p82SVfVYaWXtM86Q5tyKakiJp5KMBb9eZEGEwEtRzdLaA1F4xttWkGwgx3qKKwpifALL9fKIkwLs5Cgt3ID2Gr9LJY2nOGQHKXqpd_tadDI2qWjqmkfaaaWLypJZc3kcsKI1SfW2zrmXyl9Ib3gnmXS0M4N2-jEH6T8M6CLD4gDDTwvYBVyg7QyyrlTn9RIfwjhseNZRX8yv4T-D0wYi_LJ_bfRj-41luTPty4ba8sYGF73QUX7z2QQWyvhG1_eV_WSWZLQY28WpbUeqGMv9XxnkmqycUe72QpAGiitR9WzVlgAjw7dV5n8qGAthLOiRglePskc-oEWfds9O9OtYysKLxfe_kOYDtpSZHOtnJgXJIaQLHHGm3JAEejiCXaFaPqeISVoLol7SXQd93n3WxHxga9nY8GcTSXP__E2pB0MwKiA6Br_b795pruIaO40Iv3p-OhqOMc-fufStrORGMGexlvcl5CfJJLnPighZ1YgN-k6TxxUb3ZcgvWj5XM2Mz2bMroREjIpT1pFO9fR2S3oKqZSv45WjSsNgxI7s7hgVUIkaQs_DInbCj4BHugwlnHB1Sxt9oI3myHUNF2TrLPW6x1JDJyflMdC9PIHg_c9DziM-YMcrnYaALycYH0W3CLt_W6_Lf9mORaWFCuEQEgltySU-cfY2r-fQXUBrlnxB6007XVgIJ_W_Lo0TslhBYJK13ct0QHztNS8pIp6W512m0zBDxo3vYw6DxSjtsjbTiWtorSNvVG7Ky_MHliVZqJ1VCow2oYRbFPWfxUJfpv5OzVO_-SC7XUybHJSV2bErarmGTiZEEEPIPSIahvFoviGHECLDjui__mhd2fM8QhlsIcOdjVrOnLIR4eZaGkT22WpGaDiQ3QJM8N2oHJoeDDXD4r2l5Xk1jnmljorhOJ